-- CNBC-Fed OKs JP Morgan use of Bear collateral
-- 
-- Fri Mar 14, 2008 11:40am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/14/us-usa-bearsterns-fed-idUSWAT00913120080314

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The Federal Reserve has told JPMorgan ( JPM.N ) it can bring collateral from investment bank Bear Stearns BSC.N to the central bank's discount window as part of a government-private sector arrangement to prop Bear Stearns up, the CNBC cable television network said on Friday. 

 The Fed will not hold JP Morgan liable for any default on Bear Stearns collateral, CNBC said. (Reporting by  Mark Felsenthal ; Editing by Tom Hals)